<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Our Wedding</title><link>https://nixonpj.github.io/wedding-site/</link><description>Recent content on Our Wedding</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Sat, 29 Nov 2025 22:47:17 -0500</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://nixonpj.github.io/wedding-site/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>FAQ</title><link>https://nixonpj.github.io/wedding-site/faq/</link><pubDate>Sat, 29 Nov 2025 22:47:17 -0500</pubDate><guid>https://nixonpj.github.io/wedding-site/faq/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="accommodation-and-venue">Accommodation and Venue&lt;/h2>
&lt;h3 id="where-is-the-venue">Where is the venue?&lt;/h3>
&lt;p>&lt;a href="https://amitarasa.com">Amita Rasa&lt;/a> is a dedicated wedding venue spread over 28 acres. The venue is 1.5 hours away from Bangalore in the getaway spot of Nandi Hills.&lt;/p>
&lt;h3 id="where-can-i-stay">Where can I stay?&lt;/h3>
&lt;p>We&amp;rsquo;ve arranged for a block of rooms at three hotels near the venue. Please fill out the &lt;a href="https://nixonpj.github.io/wedding-site/rsvp/">RSVP form&lt;/a> and we will book your stay for the 26th and 27th at one of the hotels.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Itinerary</title><link>https://nixonpj.github.io/wedding-site/itinerary/</link><pubDate>Sat, 29 Nov 2025 22:47:17 -0500</pubDate><guid>https://nixonpj.github.io/wedding-site/itinerary/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="mehendi">Mehendi&lt;/h2>
&lt;div class="itinerary-section-with-image">
 &lt;div class="section-image">
 &lt;img src="https://nixonpj.github.io/wedding-site/images/mehendi.svg" alt="" style="width: 250px; max-width: 100%; height: auto;" />
 &lt;/div>
 &lt;div class="section-content">
 &lt;strong>Time:&lt;/strong> 10:00 AM&lt;br>
&lt;strong>Date:&lt;/strong> February 26, 2026&lt;br>
&lt;strong>Location:&lt;/strong> Aangan&lt;br>
&lt;strong>Duration:&lt;/strong> Approximately 2 hours&lt;br>
&lt;strong>Dress Code:&lt;/strong> Casual traditional Indian attire. Yellow, orange, or green colors are preferred.&lt;br>
&lt;strong>Description:&lt;/strong> A joyful pre-wedding ritual where intricate henna designs are applied. Light refreshments and traditional snacks will be served.
 &lt;/div>
&lt;/div>


&lt;hr>
&lt;h2 id="sangeet">Sangeet&lt;/h2>
&lt;div class="itinerary-section-with-image">
 &lt;div class="section-image">
 &lt;img src="https://nixonpj.github.io/wedding-site/images/sangeet.svg" alt="" style="width: 250px; max-width: 100%; height: auto;" />
 &lt;/div>
 &lt;div class="section-content">
 &lt;strong>Time:&lt;/strong> 6:00 PM&lt;br>
&lt;strong>Date:&lt;/strong> February 26, 2026&lt;br>
&lt;strong>Location:&lt;/strong> Aangan&lt;br>
&lt;strong>Duration:&lt;/strong> Approximately 3 hours&lt;br>
&lt;strong>Dress Code:&lt;/strong> Festive Indian attire. Bright colors and traditional outfits are encouraged.&lt;br>
&lt;strong>Description:&lt;/strong> An evening of music, dance, and celebration! Family and friends will perform traditional and modern dances. Dinner service included.
 &lt;/div>
&lt;/div>


&lt;hr>
&lt;h2 id="haldi">Haldi&lt;/h2>
&lt;div class="itinerary-section-with-image">
 &lt;div class="section-image">
 &lt;img src="https://nixonpj.github.io/wedding-site/images/marigold.svg" alt="" style="width: 250px; max-width: 100%; height: auto;" />
 &lt;/div>
 &lt;div class="section-content">
 &lt;strong>Time:&lt;/strong> 11:00 AM&lt;br>
&lt;strong>Date:&lt;/strong> February 27, 2026&lt;br>
&lt;strong>Location:&lt;/strong> Kalyani&lt;br>
&lt;strong>Duration:&lt;/strong> Approximately 2 hours&lt;br>
&lt;strong>Dress Code:&lt;/strong> Yellow or cream-colored traditional Indian attire. Please avoid wearing your best clothes as turmeric may stain.&lt;br>
&lt;strong>Description:&lt;/strong> A traditional pre-wedding ritual where turmeric paste is applied to the bride and groom. An intimate family ceremony with blessings and light breakfast.
 &lt;/div>
&lt;/div>


